{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee776-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s1111"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1111"},"text":"§ 1111.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Improving economy and efficiency","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"To improve economy and efficiency in the United States Government, the President shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee777-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s1111/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" make a study of each agency to decide, and may send Congress recommendations, on changes that should be made in—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee778-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s1111/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the organization, activities, and business methods of agencies;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee779-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s1111/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" agency appropriations;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee77a-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s1111/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the assignment of particular activities to particular services; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee77b-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s1111/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" regrouping of services; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee77c-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s1111/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" evaluate and develop improved plans for the organization, coordination, and management of the executive branch of the Government.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbcfee77d-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/913"},"text":"96 Stat. 913","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbcfee77e-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idbcfee77f-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idbcfee780-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"1111","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:18.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1921-06-10/ch18/s209"},"text":"June 10, 1921, ch. 18, § 209","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/22"},"text":"42 Stat. 22","children":[],"tail":"; Reorg. Plan No. 1 of 1939, eff. "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 1, 1939","children":[],"tail":", § 1, "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1423"},"text":"53 Stat. 1423","children":[],"tail":"; Reorg. Plan No. 2 of 1970, eff. "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":", § 102(a), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/2085"},"text":"84 Stat. 2085","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:18a.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-12/ch946/s104"},"text":"Sept. 12, 1950, ch. 946, § 104","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/834"},"text":"64 Stat. 834","children":[],"tail":"; Reorg. Plan No. 2 of 1970, eff. "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":", § 102(a), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/2085"},"text":"84 Stat. 2085","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the section, before clause (1), the words “To improve economy and efficiency in the United States Government” are substituted for “(with a view of securing greater economy and efficiency in the conduct of the public service)” in 31:18 and “with a view to efficient and economical service” in 31:18a to eliminate unnecessary words. The word “President” is substituted for “Office of Management and Budget, when directed by the President” in 31:18 and “President, through the Director of the Office of Management and Budget” in 31:18a because sections 101 and 102(a) of Reorganization Plan No. 2 of 1970 (eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/2085"},"text":"84 Stat. 2085","children":[],"tail":") designated the Bureau of the Budget as the Office of Management and Budget and transferred all functions of the Bureau to the President. In clause (1), the words “existing” and “detailed” are omitted as surplus."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idbd013171-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbd013172-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Regulatory Reductions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For provisions requiring executive departments and agencies to undertake to eliminate not less than 50 percent of its civilian internal management regulations not required by law, see Ex. Ord. No. 12861, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-09-11"},"text":"Sept. 11, 1993","children":[],"tail":", 58 F.R. 48255, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s601"},"text":"section 601 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
